50|$|The IAO began funding {{research}} and development of the Total Information Awareness (TIA) Program in February 2003 but renamed the program the <b>Terrorism</b> <b>Information</b> <b>Awareness</b> Program in May that year after an adverse media reaction to the program's implications for public surveillance. Although TIA was only one of several IAO projects, many critics and news reports conflated TIA with other related research projects of the IAO, with the result that TIA came in popular usage to stand for an entire subset of IAO programs.|$|E
